Abstract = {{The dynamics of wolf attacks on domestic ungulates at the levels of
   population group (the region of Central Forest Nature Reserve) and
   population (Tver oblast) have been analyzed over the period of 1971 to
   2015. It has been found that the frequency of attacks increases during
   the phase of predator population growth under the effect of qualitative
   changes within the population. An increase in the frequency of attacks
